New Records: Nathan Eovaldi struck out 10 batters and held the Chicago White Sox to one hit and two walks over seven innings.
Texas Rangers completed a three-game sweep of the Chicago White Sox, a team record.
Key Match Events: Corey Seager's solo homer in the fourth inning gave Texas a 1-0 lead.
Andrew Benintendi's homer against Rangers closer Kirby Yates in the ninth inning pulled Chicago to within 2-1.
Nathan Eovaldi's one-hit performance was a standout moment.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Texas Rangers had not won three consecutive games since July 25 before this series.
